Minimum certificates to connect to google.
It is provided at https://pki.goog/roots.pem.


DST_Root_CA_X3.pem is needed to connect service using
google managed certificates
https://cloud.google.com/load-balancing/docs/ssl-certificates#managed-certs
As of Nov 2018, it's certificates generated by Let's Encrypt.
https://letsencrypt.org/certificates/
DST_Root_CA_X3 can be found in various places.
- https://www.identrust.com/support/downloads
  https://www.identrust.com/node/935

```
 $ openssl pkcs7 -print_certs -inform der -in trustidrootx3_chain.p7b \
  > DST_Root_CA_X3.pem
```

